JSE-listed Long4Life has appointed Mireille Levenstein CFO, effective November 1. She will succeed Peter Riskowitz, who is retiring on October 31. Having spent 16 years as CFO of Paracon Holdings, a company previously listed on the JSE, she has extensive experience in financial strategy, operational management and corporate finance. After the acquisition of Paracon by Adcorp Holdings, Levenstein also served as a director on the boards of several subsidiary companies of Adcorp. Prior to this period, she was a partner at Grant Thornton.